    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "A verdict was rendered against\nthe Northern Pacific railroad in\nJudge Hinkle's court today for\n$4,000 damages. Augusta Steffans\nand her minor children being the\nplaintiffs.\n\n\nMichael Steffans, the husband\nand father, was killed October 80,\n1907, by jumping from train on\nwhich he was a passenger. The\ntrain had got beyond control of the\ncrew, which so alarmed the passen-\ngers that several of them jumped.\nSuit was brought for 100000\ndamages and the verdict of today Is\nin the nature of a compromise."
    }
